HEADWORD: Asterias
<hw>As*te"ri*as</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ starred, fr. <grk>'asth`r</grk> star.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A genus of echinoderms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Formerly the group of this name included nearly all
starfishes and ophiurans. Now it is restricted to a genus including the
commonest shore starfishes.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Asteriated</ent>⟦br⟧
